{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"halfbare-violent-peccary","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nPersist a bounded bug-classification enum at close, replacing today's validated-then-discarded free-text `--reason`. Adds a `--class` param to `transition` and threads it into the STATUS event `status_data` so it survives, with the vocabulary that feeds the classification metrics.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` ŌĆö parse a new `--class <value>` flag in `_parse_flags` (alongside `--reason`).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/txn.py` ŌĆö validate the enum for bug closes (replacing `bug_close_reason_ok`) and write `close_class` into `status_data` (currently the reason is discarded).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py` ŌĆö thread `close_class` through the close path.\n- `src/rebar/schemas/ticket_state.schema.json` ŌĆö add optional `close_class`.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/help/transition.txt`, `docs/ticket-model.md`, `docs/user-guide.md` ŌĆö document the enum.\n- `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_bug_close_class.py` ŌĆö new.\n\n## Approach\nThe bug-close reason is required today but never persisted (`txn.py` validates then drops it at status_data build), so replacing it with a bounded enum written into `status_data` is friction-neutral-to-negative and turns wasted input into a hard signal. Closed MECE vocabulary with an escape + hygiene values: `regression`, `plan_defect`, `env_integration`, `flaky`, `preexisting`, `not_a_bug`, `duplicate`, `escalated`, `undetermined`. `escalated` preserves today's Escalated branch; the rest refine Fixed. Additive/optional field (readers tolerate absence); back-out = stop requiring/writing it.\n\n## Tests\n- CLI (real subprocess): closing a bug with `--class regression` persists `close_class=regression` on the STATUS event; an invalid class is rejected; `undetermined` is always accepted.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_bug_close_class.py` passes: `rebar transition <bug> in_progress closed --class regression` exits 0 and `rebar show <bug> --output json | jq -e '.close_class==\"regression\"'` matches.\n- [ ] a value outside the enum is rejected with a nonzero exit naming the allowed values ŌĆö CLI test asserts exit != 0.\n- [ ] closing with `--class undetermined` succeeds (escape value) ŌĆö CLI test asserts exit 0.","id":"ed13-e224-1ece-44ff","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","schema"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Persist a bug close --class enum (replacing the discarded reason)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416767932856001,"uuid":"794bfb4e-4e2e-4863-9d21-895169b9566d"}